description:
Infested: Series 2

Health-Medical Documentary hosted by Eric Meyers, published by Discovery Channel in 2012 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Infested: Series 2
Infested unearths real-life horror stories of homes crawling with cockroaches, over-run with rats, invaded by bedbugs, and plagued by vermin hazardous to your physical and mental health. Determined to claim family homes as their own, these invaders use overwhelming numbers, sustained attacks and the threat of disease to conquer houses and apartments. Homes become battlegrounds, leaving their human victims with no place to hide. First-hand accounts and dramatic recreations reveal the pain and anguish of each family s fight to reclaim their homes as their own, but no matter what the outcome, home will never feel the same again.




5)  Night Terrors 
In Texas, a mother, her son, and her boyfriend enjoy life in a seemingly nice apartment. One night, though, the son is suddenly awakened by strange noises. The family try to forget about it, but more noises come in. It is soon clear that possums have been living in the walls. As if this isn't unsettling enough, the family starts getting bitten by fleas. In Pennsylvania, a mother and her three children start over in a house after living in a homeless shelter for so long. One of the children wanted a pet, so the mother brings a kitten into the house. When one of her children starts scratching, returning the kitten seems to be the solution. However, when the family starts getting itchiness and bites, it becomes clear that the house is infested with bedbugs. Their problems become so bad that the mother resorts to camping out in the yard with her children. In southern California, a married couple enjoy life in a house in a seemingly safe neighbourhood. Suddenly, the family starts hearing noises. Traps are put in the attic, and seeing a rat trapped, the family realizes that they are dealing with a rat infestation.

6)  Spreading Too Fast 
In Massachusetts, a pair of owners of a summer camp have been enjoying their dynamic jobs for a while, when suddenly, a counselor and kids from a certain lodge come in with itchy bites. The problem initially appears to be scabies, but more and more kids from different lodges come in with the same bites. It becomes clear that there is a bed bug infestation. In Arizona, a young couple and their children finally start a new life in their own apartment, only to start noticing strange things about their home. Their neighbours are frequently moving out, and they start finding bugs and brown dirt like stuff on the floor. They soon learn that cockroaches have taken over their home, leaving plenty of feces behind. In Boston, Massachusetts, a music teacher and her dog live peacefully in their home, until suddenly, they start hearing noises. After smelling a foul odor in the house, the music teacher discovers a dead rat. Soon, more and more rats show up, spreading throughout her house, even as she gets them killed.

7)  Under Siege 
In Tennessee, a family enjoy a summer vacation in the countryside. Inside their house, though, everyone starts hearing strange noises, and feces are being discovered outside and in the attic. The culprit animal turns out to be a colony of an endangered bat species living in the attic, producing waste that causes the family to get asthma. In Maryland, a pair of newlyweds buys a home together as quickly as they can, only to find something strange about their new house. Smelling a foul odor and seeing brown granules in certain spots, the couple discover cave crickets in their basement. Pest control treatments appear to work, but the crickets keep on coming. In Indiana, a married couple and their children move to a bigger home to make room for their growing family, when suddenly, the mother/wife finds spiders. At first, it doesn't seem to be a big problem, but the spiders, which turn out to be brown recluse ones, keep coming and prove to be incredibly difficult to get rid of.

